nstalls the host binaries to\n`~/.local/bin/`, and starts the daemon. You can change the install prefix:\n\n```\nmake install PREFIX=/usr/local\n```\n\nMake sure the install prefix is on your `PATH`:\n\n```\nexport PATH=\"$HOME/.local/bin:$PATH\"\n```\n\n## `go install`\n\nIf you have Go installed, you can install the host binaries directly:\n\n```\ngo install github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/cmd/cloche@latest\ngo install github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/cmd/cloched@latest\n```\n\nThis places the binaries in `$GOPATH/bin` (or `$HOME/go/bin` by default).\n\n**Important:** You must also build the Docker image — Cloche cannot run\nworkflows without it. Clone the repository and run:\n\n```\ngit clone https://github.com/cloche-dev/cloche.git\ncd cloche\nmake docker-build\n```\n\n## Pre-built Release Binaries\n\n> **Planned** — Pre-built release binaries are not yet available. This section\n> describes the intended installation method once GitHub Releases are set up.\n\nDownload pre-built binaries from the GitHub Releases page. Each release will\ninclude archives for Linux amd64, Linux arm64, macOS amd64, and macOS arm64.\n\n```\n# Example: Linux amd64\ncurl -LO https://github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/releases/latest/download/cloche-linux-amd64.tar.gz\ntar xzf cloche-linux-amd64.tar.gz\nsudo install cloche cloched /usr/local/bin/\n```\n\nYou still need to build the Docker image. Clone the repo and run\n`make docker-build`.\n\n## Homebrew (macOS / Linux)\n\n> **Planned** — A Homebrew tap is not yet published. This section describes the\n> intended installation method once the tap is available.\n\n```\nbrew tap cloche-dev/tap\nbrew install cloche\n```\n\nThis will install the host binaries (`cloche` and `cloched`). You still need\nthe Docker image — the formula will print post-install instructions for building\nit.\n\n## Verifying the Installation\n\nAfter installing, verify that everything works:\n\n```\n# Check the binaries\ncloche --help\ncloched --help\n\n# Start the daemon (if not already running)\ncloched &\n\n# Ensure the agent Docker image exists\ndocker images cloche-agent:latest\n\n# Run a quick test from any git repository with a .cloche/ directory\ncloche list\n```\n\n## Upgrading\n\nTo upgrade an existing installation, repeat your original installation method.\nIf you built from source:\n\n```\ncd cloche\ngit pull\nmake install\n```\n\nThe `make install` target stops the running daemon, installs the new binaries,\nrebuilds the Docker image, and restarts the daemon automatically.\n\n## Next Steps\n\n- [Usage guide](USAGE.md) — quick start, CLI reference, and workflow setup\n- [Workflow DSL reference](workflows.md) — full syntax for `.cloche` files\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":10,"oldLines":6,"newStart":10,"newLines":29,"lines":[" - **Git** — result extraction uses git worktrees"," - **`ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`** — for agent steps using Claude Code"," ","+For building from source, you also need:","+","+- **Go 1.25.3+** — matching the version in `go.mod`","+","+Note: Node.js and npm are only needed *inside* the container image (for Claude","+Code). You do **not** need to install them on the host — the Docker image build","+handles this automatically.","+","+## Architecture: What Runs Where","+","+Understanding which components run on the host vs inside containers helps","+clarify what you need to install:","+","+| Component | Where it runs | Notes |","+|---|---|---|","+| `cloche` (CLI) | Host | Sends commands to the daemon over gRPC |","+| `cloched` (Daemon) | Host | Manages container lifecycle and state |","+| `cloche-agent` | Inside containers only | Built into the `cloche-agent:latest` Docker image |","+","+You only need `cloche` and `cloched` on your host. The `cloche-agent` binary is","+compiled into the Docker image during `make docker-build` and never needs to be","+installed on the host.","+"," ## Build from Source"," "," Clone the repository, build the binaries and Docker image, and install them:"]},{"oldStart":21,"oldLines":7,